## GraphQL Layer

The GraphQL endpoint is powered by [Strawberry](https://strawberry.rocks/)
and follows the same hexagonal architecture as REST routes.

```
ports/graphql/
  context.py       # GraphQLContext — BaseContext subclass with DI access
  dataloaders.py   # Per-request DataLoaders for N+1 prevention
  extensions.py    # Schema extensions (QueryDepthLimiter)
  mutations.py     # Root Mutation type
  permissions.py   # IsAuthenticated permission class
  queries.py       # Root Query type
  router.py        # ProductionGraphQLRouter (error masking, structlog)
  schema.py        # strawberry.Schema assembly
{%- if use_graphql_subscriptions %}
  subscriptions.py # Root Subscription type (WebSocket transport)
{%- endif %}
  types.py         # Strawberry object / input types
```

### GraphQL Design Principles

- **Thin resolvers**: Resolvers delegate to the application service
  layer; no domain logic lives inside GraphQL types.
- **DataLoaders**: Batch database fetches are used to prevent N+1
  queries. Each DataLoader is instantiated per-request in the context.
- **Query depth limiting**: A Strawberry 'SchemaExtension' rejects
  deeply nested queries to prevent denial-of-service abuse.
- **Error masking**: In production mode, internal errors are replaced
  with a generic message while full details are logged.
- **Permission classes**: Strawberry's `BasePermission` is used for
  field-level authorization (e.g. `IsAuthenticated`).
{%- if api_style == 'both' %}
- **Coexistence with REST**: Both transports share the same application
  services, ensuring consistent business logic regardless of API style.
{%- endif %}

See [GRAPHQL.md](GRAPHQL.md) for the full GraphQL reference.
{%- endif %}


