## AI Module Architecture

The `ai/` directory implements a secondary **hexagonal layer** specifically for
AI/ML functionality.  It follows the same ports & adapters pattern: core
interfaces live in `core/interfaces/` and concrete adapters live in `ai/`.

```
ai/
  agents/          # Agent framework (ReAct, ToolCalling, LangGraph orchestrator)
  chains/          # LangChain LCEL / LlamaIndex / Summarization / Refinement chains
  config.py        # AI settings and defaults
  document_loaders/# File, web, and framework-specific loaders
  embeddings/      # Embedding adapters via LiteLLM (OpenAI, Azure, 50+) + SentenceTransformers
  evaluation/      # LLM output quality assessment (LLM-as-judge, batch scoring)
  guardrails/      # Input/output safety validation (rule-based, LLM-based)
  knowledge_graph/ # NetworkX (local) + Neo4j (production) + RDFLib (RDF/SPARQL) + LLM extraction + external KGs (Wikidata, DBpedia, ConceptNet)
  llm/             # LLM adapters via LiteLLM (OpenAI, Azure, Anthropic, 100+) + gateway
  mcp/             # Model Context Protocol server + client (streamable-http transport)
  memory/          # Conversation memory (in-memory, Redis, PostgreSQL)
  models/          # Pydantic request/response models (shared contract for routes/services)
  observability/   # AI tracing and telemetry (structlog, OpenTelemetry)
  prompts/         # Prompt templates (Jinja2-based) + manager/registry
  rag/             # RAG pipelines (ingestion, vector/graph/ensemble retrievers, reranker)
    retrievers/    # Vector, graph, ensemble, LlamaIndex retrievers
    rerankers/     # Cross-encoder reranker (sentence-transformers)
  services/        # AIService, RAGService
  text_splitter.py # Recursive text splitting
  tools/           # Agent/MCP tools (search, ingest, calculator, web_search, database_query)
  vector_stores/   # FAISS, pgvector, Azure AI Search adapters
  workflows/       # LangGraph StateGraph workflow engine (durable, checkpointed)
                   #   checkpointers.py — PostgreSQL (prod) / SQLite (staging) / memory (dev)
```

